What you need to know:

The Nets won the battle between two of the NBA's most potent offences on Saturday night despite losing James Harden to a nagging hamstring injury in the first minute of the gameAntetokounmpo, the two-time reigning NBA Most Valuable Player, played 35 minutes, shooting 16 of 24 from the floor and grabbing 11 rebounds for the underdog BucksThe Nets are 20-17 without Harden and 29-7 with him in the lineup